  "prompt": "How do you bake frozen hash browns?",
  "response": "Here's a simple method to bake frozen hash browns:\n\n1. Preheat the oven to 425\u00b0F (220\u00b0C)\n\n2. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or lightly grease it\n\n3. Spread frozen hash browns in a single layer on the baking sheet\n\n4. Optional: Lightly season with salt and pepper\n\n5. Bake for 15-20 minutes, flipping them halfway through cooking\n\n6. They're done when golden brown and crispy\n\nTips:\n- Don't thaw before cooking\n- Don't overcrowd the baking sheet\n- For extra crispiness, use a wire rack on the baking sheet\n- Cooking times may vary slightly depending on your oven and the brand of hash browns",
